cs.HC, cs.IR, cs.DL, cs.DB, cs.CL

The paper describes a 3D interface for visualizing and browsing World-Wide Web information, which involves information gathering and processing agents. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses mathematical theory to conceptually cluster objects and create a three-dimensional layout of information nodes, which suggests that it could also belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Data Mining (cs.DL) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of attributes such as location, title, keywords, topic, size, or modification time to classify and categorize documents, which suggests that it could belong to the Database (cs.DB) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of a visualization shell as an ergonomically sound user interface for exploring the information space, which suggests that it could also belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category.
